30:47.062 --> 30:48.455
Alfie been in?

30:48.498 --> 30:51.153
No. The usual?

31:45.642 --> 31:48.123
CURZON :
Help.

31:50.038 --> 31:51.953
Help!

32:34.474 --> 32:36.389
Who's there?

32:43.744 --> 32:46.225
Who is it?

32:47.356 --> 32:50.142
Pennyworth,

32:50.185 --> 32:51.882
is that you?

33:01.457 --> 33:03.894
Good morning.

33:05.200 --> 33:07.768
Good morning.

33:07.811 --> 33:09.683
We meet at last,

33:09.726 --> 33:11.859
as they say.

33:13.948 --> 33:16.429
Cat got your tongue?

33:17.734 --> 33:19.345
I thought,
when I finally met you,

33:19.388 --> 33:21.347
I'd have lots to say to you.

33:21.390 --> 33:23.784
Questions to ask.

33:23.827 --> 33:25.438
But now we're here,

33:25.481 --> 33:27.831
I've got nothing.

33:27.875 --> 33:29.398
You're nothing.

33:31.444 --> 33:34.055
You fool.

33:34.099 --> 33:35.970
You think you've won.

33:36.014 --> 33:38.233
Don't you?

33:38.277 --> 33:42.063
You really think a dirty,
stupid little pleb like you

33:42.107 --> 33:44.457
could outwit a man
of noble blood?

33:44.500 --> 33:46.676
Nah.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.939
I know there's no winning
this game.

33:48.983 --> 33:51.986
But you got to play to
the whistle, haven't you?

33:53.335 --> 33:55.250
Isn't that right,
Inspector Aziz?!

33:59.298 --> 34:01.213
You can show yourself.

34:02.344 --> 34:04.216
I've got no backup.

34:04.259 --> 34:05.260
You're safe.

34:05.304 --> 34:07.958
Come have a chat to me.

34:10.222 --> 34:12.093
I'm not a fucking idiot.

34:12.137 --> 34:14.356
I know a trap when I see one.

34:16.445 --> 34:17.794
AZIZ:
Why did you walk

34:17.838 --> 34:19.753
into it, then?

34:23.583 --> 34:25.106
I don't know.

34:25.150 --> 34:28.022
I think
I don't give a fuck anymore.

34:28.066 --> 34:29.371
AZIZ:
I'm sorry.

34:29.415 --> 34:31.373
Makes my job easier,
at any rate.

34:31.417 --> 34:33.810
I don't know about easy.

34:33.854 --> 34:35.073
You've got three men with you

34:35.116 --> 34:36.596
and another couple up there
in cover

34:36.639 --> 34:37.597
with sniper rifles.

34:37.640 --> 34:39.773
There and there.

34:39.816 --> 34:41.383
I bet I can kill
Curzon and one

34:41.427 --> 34:43.168
or two of your men
before you can kill me.

34:43.211 --> 34:44.952
I doubt that.

34:44.995 --> 34:47.041
Let's find out, shall we?

34:47.085 --> 34:48.129
Count to three.

34:48.173 --> 34:52.002
Shoot him now.

34:52.046 --> 34:53.178
Shoot him.AZIZ:
One moment, sir,

34:53.221 --> 34:55.136
please.

34:55.180 --> 34:58.835
I am genuinely sorry
for all this chicanery.

34:58.879 --> 35:00.881
His father has
political clout.

35:02.100 --> 35:03.492
You know
the rest.

35:03.536 --> 35:04.711
We have no choice.

35:04.754 --> 35:06.582
Who's "we"?
You and your conscience?

35:07.714 --> 35:09.672
My superiors have no choice.

35:09.716 --> 35:11.109
Therefore,
I have no choice.

35:11.152 --> 35:12.414
I understand.

35:12.458 --> 35:13.937
No hard feelings.

35:13.981 --> 35:15.069
Count to three.

35:15.113 --> 35:16.897
I told you
to shoot him, damn it.

35:16.940 --> 35:18.333
A direct bloody order.
Do you hear?

35:18.377 --> 35:19.465
Shut up!

35:20.857 --> 35:22.424
Listen,

35:22.468 --> 35:23.773
if you give me

35:23.817 --> 35:25.906
your word of honor
that you'll spare this man,

35:25.949 --> 35:27.560
I can let you escape,

35:27.603 --> 35:30.867
get out of
the country.

35:30.911 --> 35:31.912
What?

35:31.955 --> 35:33.957
That's not the fucking plan.

35:34.958 --> 35:36.003
Shoot him, man.
Shoot him!

35:36.046 --> 35:37.352
Quiet!

35:40.312 --> 35:42.183
That's very decent of you.

35:42.227 --> 35:43.924
Won't do, though.
He has to die.

35:43.967 --> 35:45.055
AZIZ:
Look at him!

35:45.099 --> 35:46.753
Sad little madman.

35:48.407 --> 35:49.625
Is he really worth your life?

35:49.669 --> 35:52.150
CURZON:
You wretched little insect.

35:52.193 --> 35:54.630
How dare you?
How dare you?!

35:54.674 --> 35:55.631
My father will
have you hung!

35:55.675 --> 35:56.893
Is he worth your life?

35:56.937 --> 35:58.156
No.

35:58.199 --> 36:00.984
He's not worth
anything.

36:01.028 --> 36:02.072
Not fair, is it?

36:02.116 --> 36:03.900
Count to three.

36:06.033 --> 36:07.991
Alfred, please.
I don't need to count to three.

36:08.035 --> 36:09.167
I just need
to raise my finger.

36:09.210 --> 36:10.951
Well, go ahead.
Raise your finger, then.

36:26.967 --> 36:28.447
Don't... you...

36:28.490 --> 36:29.274
dare.

36:29.317 --> 36:31.145
Drop your weapons.

36:32.015 --> 36:34.496
All of ya!

36:35.628 --> 36:36.585
Tell 'em.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.152
Do as she says.

36:51.687 --> 36:53.776
Glad to see me now,
aren't you, pet?

36:53.820 --> 36:56.431
Say I'm wrong.

37:09.096 --> 37:10.532
Stop looking.

37:10.576 --> 37:11.403
You said you had

37:11.446 --> 37:12.665
no backup.

37:12.708 --> 37:13.753
And I actually
believed you.

37:13.796 --> 37:14.754
Well played.

37:14.797 --> 37:16.103
Swear to God, Mr. Aziz,

37:16.146 --> 37:17.235
I didn't know she was here.

37:17.278 --> 37:18.975
Look at me.

37:20.150 --> 37:21.282
Who is she?

37:21.326 --> 37:23.589
Looks very familiar.Long story.

37:23.632 --> 37:24.981
You think we talk
'cause you can wait.

37:25.025 --> 37:26.069
Oi.

37:26.113 --> 37:27.636
I told you to wait.

37:27.680 --> 37:29.377
I only gave him
a few little jabs.

37:29.421 --> 37:30.639
Keep her away
from me.

37:31.684 --> 37:33.294
Big baby.

37:33.338 --> 37:35.775
Who's this, then?

37:35.818 --> 37:36.776
Who are you?

37:36.819 --> 37:37.777
I'm nobody.

37:37.820 --> 37:39.822
Nobody?

37:39.866 --> 37:41.650
Nobody? What are you
doing here, then?

37:41.694 --> 37:42.956
Tell the truth.

37:42.999 --> 37:44.784
Nanny! I'm his nanny!

37:48.527 --> 37:50.268
Is that right, duck?

37:50.311 --> 37:51.660
She's your nanny?

37:51.704 --> 37:53.532
Mm-hmm.

37:53.575 --> 37:54.794
I see, I see.

37:54.837 --> 37:56.839
You're one of them.

37:56.883 --> 37:59.407
Filthy bastards.

37:59.451 --> 38:01.191
Posh people.

38:01.235 --> 38:03.759
Perverts, the lot of 'em.

38:03.803 --> 38:05.195
It's a wonder
they reproduce.

38:05.239 --> 38:06.414
Get her away from me.

38:06.458 --> 38:07.589
She's mad!

38:07.633 --> 38:09.287
Mad?

38:09.330 --> 38:11.941
I'm calm as a
millpond, me!

38:11.985 --> 38:14.466
You ain't seen
nothing yet.

38:14.509 --> 38:16.337
Sorry,
there'll be no torture.

38:16.381 --> 38:17.469
Give over.

38:17.512 --> 38:19.079
We're not animals.

38:19.122 --> 38:20.080
Speak for yourself.

38:20.123 --> 38:21.255
I need to see him suffer.

38:22.387 --> 38:23.779
No.

38:23.823 --> 38:25.781
You're a soldier.

38:25.825 --> 38:28.175
Are you telling me
you've never had a go?

38:29.263 --> 38:31.134
I've done torture.

38:31.178 --> 38:32.614
For answers.

38:32.658 --> 38:34.355
To make people talk.

38:34.399 --> 38:36.183
This one's got
nothing to tell us.

38:36.226 --> 38:38.185
He's mental.

38:38.228 --> 38:39.229
He just needs to be dead.

38:39.273 --> 38:40.448
Oh, God. This isn't right.

38:40.492 --> 38:42.320
You owe me.

38:42.363 --> 38:43.930
You know you do.

38:45.192 --> 38:46.367
Give us ten minutes.

38:46.411 --> 38:48.369
You don't need to watch.

38:48.413 --> 38:50.110
Leave the room if
you're squeamish.

38:50.153 --> 38:52.286
No, I'm-I'm sorry.

38:52.330 --> 38:53.418
I'm-I'm sorry.

38:53.461 --> 38:54.854
I'm sick.
I know I am.

38:54.897 --> 38:56.986
I don't
deserve this!

38:58.553 --> 39:00.294
Do you not?

39:00.338 --> 39:02.427
How many other women
have you killed?

39:02.470 --> 39:04.080
Esme wasn't your first,

39:04.124 --> 39:05.517
was she?

39:07.432 --> 39:09.390
I can smell
darkness on you.

39:09.434 --> 39:11.784
I-I have a sickness.

39:11.827 --> 39:14.787
I-I swear, if you let me go,
I'll get treatment.

39:14.830 --> 39:15.875
My-my family will...

39:15.918 --> 39:16.919
Sorry, love.

39:20.401 --> 39:22.621
What the fuck?

39:22.664 --> 39:24.927
I have to say,
I'm very disappointed in you.

39:24.971 --> 39:26.494
Welcome to the club.

39:26.538 --> 39:29.062
I'm afraid this is gonna
create a lot of trouble.

39:29.105 --> 39:30.150
For all of us.

39:30.193 --> 39:33.327
Be seeing you, then.

39:40.856 --> 39:42.728
Ladies and gentlemen,

39:42.771 --> 39:45.992
it's my great honor
to introduce to you

39:46.035 --> 39:47.907
our speaker of the day,

39:47.950 --> 39:50.997
talking to you on the
subject of "A New Dawn,"

39:52.433 --> 39:55.523
pro tem leader
of the Raven Society,

39:55.567 --> 39:58.439
Dr. Frances Gaunt!

40:08.101 --> 40:11.452
Good afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

40:11.496 --> 40:13.367
Citizens of England,

40:13.411 --> 40:16.109
I will talk
to you today

40:16.152 --> 40:19.895
about the future
of our country.

40:19.939 --> 40:22.420
This is a topic
around which has settled

40:22.463 --> 40:24.639
a unanimous gloom.

40:24.683 --> 40:26.902
All seem to agree

40:26.946 --> 40:30.340
that, if we're not destroyed
by atom bombs,

40:30.384 --> 40:32.995
we will be ruined by poverty

40:33.039 --> 40:34.562
and moral decay,

40:34.606 --> 40:37.086
by unemployment and mob rule

40:37.130 --> 40:39.654
and angry dissent.

40:39.698 --> 40:43.484
We are united
only in our pessimism!

40:43.528 --> 40:47.619
Today,
I will talk to you of hope.

40:47.662 --> 40:50.926
Hope and optimism

40:50.970 --> 40:53.146
and a glorious future.

40:53.189 --> 40:55.496
Some of you will laugh,

40:55.540 --> 40:58.325
as if I'm talking about fairies and unicorns.

41:01.284 --> 41:05.201
But no.
Hope is real and powerful.

41:05.245 --> 41:09.205
Once we have hope,
then courage and strength

41:09.249 --> 41:10.555
and discipline will follow.

41:10.598 --> 41:13.427
No trial cannot be endured.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.995
No battle cannot be won.

41:16.038 --> 41:18.476
Platitudes, you say.

41:18.519 --> 41:21.130
Empty rhetoric. No.

41:22.436 --> 41:25.047
I am not here to speak of hope.

41:25.091 --> 41:26.484
I am here to show you.

41:26.527 --> 41:28.398
I'm no leader,

41:28.442 --> 41:31.706
no visionary.
I'm a simple country doctor

41:31.750 --> 41:36.102
here only because a great man
was brought low.

41:36.145 --> 41:40.149
My predecessor in this post

41:40.193 --> 41:42.412
was Lord James Harwood.

41:42.456 --> 41:44.545
He was a man of heroic vision

41:44.589 --> 41:46.547
and boundless energy.

41:46.591 --> 41:49.158
A true patriot
and a man of destiny.

41:49.202 --> 41:52.335
So the powers that be
were afraid of him

41:52.379 --> 41:55.034
and ordered his destruction.

41:55.077 --> 41:57.427
They threw him into the Tower.

41:57.471 --> 42:00.169
They kept him in a metal box,

42:00.213 --> 42:03.433
four foot square, and tortured
him to the brink of death.

42:03.477 --> 42:06.045
They mutilated him horribly.

42:06.088 --> 42:08.874
And when he was
thoroughly broken,

42:08.917 --> 42:11.224
they threw him naked
into the streets,

42:11.267 --> 42:13.182
condemned to a living death,

42:13.226 --> 42:16.185
a crazed and crippled beggar.

42:18.318 --> 42:20.494
My friends,

42:20.538 --> 42:23.062
fellow citizens,

42:23.105 --> 42:26.021
I hereby formally announce

42:26.065 --> 42:29.155
my resignation as leader
of the Raven Society,

42:29.198 --> 42:31.853
effective immediately.

42:31.897 --> 42:34.595
Where the devil is she going
with this?

42:34.639 --> 42:38.860
But it is my great honor
to introduce

42:38.904 --> 42:40.514
our new leader,

42:40.558 --> 42:42.734
our guiding light,

42:42.777 --> 42:46.433
Lord James Harwood.

42:49.392 --> 42:51.307
MAN:
What's happening?

43:03.406 --> 43:04.799
What the fuck?

43:08.673 --> 43:10.022
Oh, my God.

43:10.065 --> 43:11.501
RIPPER:
There goes

43:11.545 --> 43:12.981
our truce.

43:13.025 --> 43:15.418
Wow.

43:15.462 --> 43:17.595
Guess you were right.

43:17.638 --> 43:19.945
Situation has
deteriorated fast.

43:21.511 --> 43:22.556
Doesn't he look handsome, eh?

43:22.600 --> 43:23.992
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

43:39.617 --> 43:41.488
Hello, England.

43:51.759 --> 43:52.978
Harwood!

43:53.021 --> 43:55.502
Bravo!

43:57.156 --> 43:59.593
Read the Riot Act.
Send in the heavy brigade.

44:01.029 --> 44:02.378
Arrest him.

44:02.422 --> 44:04.990
Arrest everyone.

44:13.738 --> 44:17.219
You cannot imagine

44:17.263 --> 44:21.093
how good it is
to see you all here today.

44:21.136 --> 44:24.444
A beautiful sight.

44:24.487 --> 44:28.535
The same cannot be said for me,
I'm afraid.

44:30.406 --> 44:31.799
I hope

44:31.843 --> 44:34.367
that you will forgive my looks

44:34.410 --> 44:36.674
and listen to my message.

44:38.806 --> 44:42.897
A new dawn is coming,
my friends.

44:44.029 --> 44:45.770
A fresh start

44:45.813 --> 44:47.119
for all of us!

44:55.780 --> 44:57.303
HARWOOD:
I'm going to talk with you

44:57.346 --> 44:59.609
about the serious...

44:59.653 --> 45:02.351
...the serious problem
that is fa...

45:02.395 --> 45:03.483
POLICE CHIEF:
Our sovereign queen

45:03.526 --> 45:05.441
commands all persons
being assembled here

45:05.485 --> 45:06.704
to disperse

45:06.747 --> 45:09.315
and depart peacefully...

45:09.358 --> 45:11.404
...on penalties contained...

45:11.447 --> 45:13.754
...in the Riotous Assembly Act.

45:13.798 --> 45:15.974
MAN:
Close the door!

45:19.151 --> 45:20.239
Please, stay calm.

45:44.567 --> 45:46.569
Let's go!

45:59.844 --> 46:02.368
Stop!

46:08.722 --> 46:10.985
Officers of the law,

46:11.029 --> 46:12.857
this is England.

46:12.900 --> 46:14.815
You will respect

46:14.859 --> 46:18.427
our ancient rights
and liberties

46:18.471 --> 46:20.734
and stop this violence

46:20.778 --> 46:23.998
immediately!

46:26.261 --> 46:28.089
Stand down.

46:48.806 --> 46:50.503
Further violence was averted

46:50.546 --> 46:53.419
when the police allowed
the crowd to disperse

46:53.462 --> 46:56.422
peacefully to their homes
without arrest.

46:56.465 --> 46:58.467
As we continue the news...

46:58.511 --> 47:01.253
Double whiskey
and two aspirin, please, Sid.

47:01.296 --> 47:03.211
Got it.

47:03.255 --> 47:05.431
You'll never guess
who was on the telly.

47:05.474 --> 47:07.825
I'll never guess.

47:07.868 --> 47:11.002
You look... pale, Alfie.

47:11.045 --> 47:12.307
You all right?

47:12.351 --> 47:15.136
Yeah, just a bit
of a headache, that's all.

47:15.180 --> 47:17.312
We looked
for that Mrs. Pike all over.

47:17.356 --> 47:19.445
Not hide nor hair.

47:20.576 --> 47:22.622
Yeah.

47:22.665 --> 47:25.059
Forget about all that. Sorted.

47:25.103 --> 47:27.279
Sorted? Curzon?

47:32.719 --> 47:34.634
SID:
You missed a prime show
on the telly, Alfie.

47:34.677 --> 47:37.028
High drama.

47:37.071 --> 47:38.986
Did I?

47:44.862 --> 47:46.733
See you later.

48:00.747 --> 48:01.966
MR. PENNYWORTH:
We'll not tell him anything.

48:03.097 --> 48:04.229
But...

48:04.272 --> 48:06.057
No. No, no, he'll make a fuss.

48:09.930 --> 48:11.540
You all right, Dad?Ah.

48:11.584 --> 48:12.977
Yeah, it's nothing.

48:13.020 --> 48:14.674
Bumped into a door.

48:15.936 --> 48:17.024
Clumsy so-and-so,

48:17.068 --> 48:18.852
he is.

48:20.941 --> 48:22.638
Where have you been?

48:22.682 --> 48:24.249
You don't look very well.

48:26.120 --> 48:28.079
Give us a hug, Mum.

48:28.122 --> 48:30.908
Oh, course.

48:33.736 --> 48:35.651
What about me, then?

48:37.088 --> 48:38.480
You're in a good mood.

48:38.524 --> 48:39.873
Why not?

48:39.917 --> 48:41.266
Today was a good day.

48:41.309 --> 48:42.702
If you say so.

48:42.745 --> 48:44.182
And tomorrow...

48:44.225 --> 48:46.967
tomorrow will be even better.

48:47.011 --> 48:48.577
I hope you're right.

48:48.621 --> 48:49.970
I know I am, son.

48:50.014 --> 48:52.277
I know I am.

48:52.320 --> 48:53.974
We've had a rough go of it,

48:54.018 --> 48:56.585
you know, all in all.

48:56.629 --> 48:58.587
But things are
gonna change now.

49:01.025 --> 49:03.331
Well, Prime Minister,

49:03.375 --> 49:04.985
that didn't go
very well, did it?

49:05.029 --> 49:07.335
No, ma'am. It did not.

49:07.379 --> 49:08.989
I could swear you told
me Harwood was dead

49:09.033 --> 49:10.730
months and months ago.

49:10.773 --> 49:13.124
"As good as dead," ma'am.

49:13.167 --> 49:15.735
"As good as," I said.

49:15.778 --> 49:18.781
Says here
Harwood's a national sensation,

49:18.825 --> 49:20.218
a hero,

49:20.261 --> 49:22.611
darling
of the disaffected masses.

49:22.655 --> 49:24.613
Says he defied
the police by

49:24.657 --> 49:28.922
"sheer force
of his commanding authority."

49:28.966 --> 49:32.360
Well, perhaps with water cannon
and rubber bullets,

49:32.404 --> 49:33.883
something might have been done.

49:33.927 --> 49:36.016
Oh, it's my fault, is it?

49:36.060 --> 49:37.670
Certainly not, madam.

49:37.713 --> 49:40.586
I-I merely point out
the mitigating circumstances.

49:40.629 --> 49:44.024
In any case, thrash the bugger
in Trafalgar Square.

49:44.068 --> 49:47.506
Make an example.Well, I would
that were possible.

49:47.549 --> 49:49.203
He's far too high-profile.

49:49.247 --> 49:52.119
Detain him now,
we'll have a tiger by the tail.

49:52.163 --> 49:54.252
The press
will scream blue murder.

49:54.295 --> 49:56.645
There'll be angry mobs in the
street howling for his liberty.

49:56.689 --> 49:58.560
Well, what are we
going to do, then?

49:58.604 --> 50:01.607
I don't know, Your Majesty.

50:01.650 --> 50:03.565
You'd better think
of something

50:03.609 --> 50:05.437
bloody fast.

50:07.482 --> 50:08.657
I got it!Got it?

50:08.701 --> 50:10.877
Yes. Ha. Oh, again?Hey! Bravo.

50:10.920 --> 50:13.184
Oh, I've got it! I've got it!

50:13.227 --> 50:16.317
Oh, what did I... what
did I tell you, Frances?

50:16.361 --> 50:17.536
I never doubted you.

50:17.579 --> 50:18.885
Oh, didn't you?

50:18.928 --> 50:20.408
Good girl. I-I've
got to confess

50:20.452 --> 50:22.106
I doubted myself.

50:22.149 --> 50:24.804
I'm just jolly lucky that
I'm not hanging in a dungeon.

50:24.847 --> 50:25.848
Hear, hear.

50:25.892 --> 50:27.154
Sir,

50:27.198 --> 50:28.242
your guests have arrived.

50:28.286 --> 50:29.722
Oh, uh, jolly good.

50:29.765 --> 50:31.680
They're a touch early. Will
you stall them a moment?

50:31.724 --> 50:32.942
Yes, Your Lordship.

50:32.986 --> 50:35.075
Guests?

50:35.119 --> 50:37.121
Yes.

50:37.164 --> 50:39.514
You see, the question
is, Frances, what now?

50:39.558 --> 50:41.647
Yes, indeed.

50:41.690 --> 50:44.128
See, I see power
within our grasp.

50:44.171 --> 50:46.260
And when that day comes,
some cold, hard decisions

50:46.304 --> 50:47.783
will have to be made.

50:47.827 --> 50:50.917
Some people will be with us,
and some against.

50:50.960 --> 50:52.614
I'm confident about
the army and the clergy,

50:52.658 --> 50:55.835
but Her Majesty the Queen...

50:55.878 --> 50:57.445
she troubles me.

50:57.489 --> 50:59.969
The queen?

51:00.013 --> 51:01.145
Well, I-I thought we were agreed

51:01.188 --> 51:02.624
she must be assured
of our loyalty.

51:02.668 --> 51:04.931
And we must be assured
of her obedience.

51:04.974 --> 51:07.847
Now, I know you're not keen
on going down this road,

51:07.890 --> 51:09.283
but I see no alternative.

51:09.327 --> 51:12.243
Down which road?

51:12.286 --> 51:15.202
You do trust me,
don't you, Frances?

51:15.246 --> 51:17.117
Yes, yes, of course I do.

51:17.161 --> 51:21.295
Well, if the queen should
prove to be reluctant,

51:21.339 --> 51:23.341
then we will need to find
an alternative.

51:23.384 --> 51:25.256
We will need to find
a replacement.

51:25.299 --> 51:28.085
SERVANT:
Their graces, the Duke and
Duchess of Windermere.

51:28.128 --> 51:29.260
Ah.

51:33.916 --> 51:36.267
HARWOOD:
Welcome, sir, ma'am.

51:36.310 --> 51:38.225
Welcome back to your lands.

51:57.375 --> 51:59.420
ALFRED:
Hello, Ez.

52:01.466 --> 52:03.859
Sorry I haven't visited
for a while.

52:07.602 --> 52:09.387
If you're there,
I expect you'll know

52:09.430 --> 52:11.432
that I killed the people who...

52:11.476 --> 52:13.391
Well, you know.

52:15.349 --> 52:17.569
Had to be done,
and now I've done it.

52:23.183 --> 52:25.838
You remember that first time
we went out?

52:28.232 --> 52:31.104
We were in the park,
listening to a brass band,

52:31.148 --> 52:32.584
and I made you laugh.

52:32.627 --> 52:35.282
And you looked at me
in my eyes,

52:35.326 --> 52:37.806
and you smiled at me.

52:37.850 --> 52:42.028
One of your proper
happy smiles.

52:42.071 --> 52:44.596
First one you ever gave me.

52:46.380 --> 52:49.296
I thought, fuck a duck,
she likes me.

52:51.472 --> 52:53.953
Best moment of my life,
that was.

52:53.996 --> 52:56.216
Best moment.

52:59.741 --> 53:03.571
Used to be that
that memory made me sad.

53:03.615 --> 53:07.140
I woke up this morning,
and I remembered it,

53:07.184 --> 53:10.317
and it didn't make me sad.

53:10.361 --> 53:13.712
I saw you smile at me.

53:16.280 --> 53:18.804
I sort of smiled back.

53:20.109 --> 53:23.025
So that's good, isn't it?

53:23.069 --> 53:25.332
Things are looking up.

